Sure! Below is a simple HTML web application that uses A-Frame to display a 3D model loaded from the specified URL. It includes embedded CSS for basic styling and JavaScript for initializing the model once it's downloaded.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>A-Frame 3D Model Example</title>
    <style>
        body { margin: 0; }
        a-scene { height: 100vh; }
        .loading { color: white; text-align: center; position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%); }
    </style>
    <script src="https://aframe.io/releases/1.2.0/aframe.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="loading" id="loading">Loading model...</div>
    <a-scene embedded>
        <a-entity id="model" gltf-model="https://api.syte.ms/api/3d/gltf/DENW49AL00009XTV" position="0 0 0" scale="0.1 0.1 0.1"></a-entity>
        <a-sky color="#ECECEC"></a-sky>
        <a-light type="ambient" color="#FFF" intensity="0.5"></a-light>
        <a-light type="directional" color="#FFF" intensity="1" position="-1 1 1"></a-light>
        <a-camera position="0 1.6 3"></a-camera>
    </a-scene>

    <script>
        window.onload = function() {
            const model = document.querySelector('#model');
            const loadingText = document.getElementById('loading');

            model.addEventListener('model-loaded', () => {
                loadingText.style.display = 'none'; // Hide loading text once the model has been loaded.
            });

            model.addEventListener('model-error', () => {
                loadingText.innerHTML = 'Failed to load model';
            });
        };
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
1. **Basic A-Frame Setup**: This HTML file includes the A-Frame library and creates a scene. The scene consists of an entity that attempts to load the GLTF model from the provided API.
2. **Loading Indicator**: A div is shown while the model is being loaded. Once the model loads successfully, the loading text is hidden.
3. **Camera and Lights**: A camera and a couple of light sources are included to make the scene more visually appealing.
4. **Model Error Handling**: If the model fails to load, an error message is displayed.

You can copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser to see the 3D model loaded into the A-Frame scene.
